channel.name: ❔about
channel.topic: What this server is about! (Basically the advertisement for this server)

messages.content:
--= **Knowledge Base** =--
> a Discord Server for Commanders, Datapackers, Resource Packers or anyone who wants to begin/learn

**Content:**
• A compiled list of Tools and Generators for Resource Packs, Commands, and Datapacks.
• FAQs in the industry and answers to said questions
• Pros and Cons to common debates
• A list of acronyms commonly and what they stand for
• Lists of Text Editor Plugins for making Datapacks
• A list of discord servers to ask for help with Plugins, Modding, Playtesting and Redstone
• The community is fun and cursed but only in #general

**Server:**
• Reaction Roles to hide unwanted channels, reveal extra channels, and tell us to not ping you
• Getting pinged is always voluntary through Reaction Roles, this means `@here`/`@everyone` is NEVER used
• **You can swear here!**

**Invite Link:** 
https://discord.gg/xpNJdH9

--= **What happened to Tools & Resources category?** =--
We decided that using Channels is not the best way to store or access our Resources, and plan to move it to a website.

HOWEVER while that website is still being setup __all our resources are temporarily stored on a GitHub repository here__ 
> 🔗 https://github.com/SheepCommander/KnowledgeBase

**What's GitHub?**
GitHub is a way to share and view files on the internet and allow the community to easily suggest changes.

**How do you use it?**
To navigate it is much the same as navigating a bunch of files. Go to the website, click on `1.16.4` then find what resource you want. 
Each resource has a `viewable-github-paste.md` and a `raw-discord-paste.txt`. I hope I don't have to explain what this means.

**Some other plans**
Bots @Knowledge Bot and @MMK21Games that are meant to be able to grab resources from the GitHub and send them here.

I also plan to setup "triggers"/"auto responders" on good ol' @Carl-bot to automatically answer easily solved questions.
